<!-- About Area
============================================ -->

<div id="blog-area" class="pricing-area gray-bg ptb-50">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-lg-12 text-center">
                <div class="title-style title-pb2">
                    <h1>Helpy <span> Blog</span></h1>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="row">
            @foreach (var post in Model)
            {
                <div class="col-lg-4 col-md-4 col-12">
                    <div class="single-price-package">
                        <div class="price-title">
                            <h3>@Html.Raw(post.Title.Rendered)</h3>
                        </div>
                        <div class="post-content">
                            @if (post.RttpgFeaturedImageUrl != null)
                            {
                                <img src="@(post.RttpgFeaturedImageUrl?.Full?[0]?.ToString())" alt="@post.Title.Rendered" style="max-width: 100%; height: auto;" />
                            }

                            <p>
                                <span class="text-bottom">@Html.Raw(post.Excerpt.Rendered)</span>
                            </p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="price-list">
                            <a class="btn btn-success" href="@post.Link" target="_blank">Read more</a>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            }

        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<div id="support-area" class="contact-area  pt-120">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-lg-12 text-center">
                <div class="title-style title-pb">
                    <h1>get in<span> touch</span></h1>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="ms-auto me-auto col-lg-8 text-center">
                <div class="contact-from">
                    <form id="contact-form" action="" method="post">
                        <input name="name" id="name" type="text" placeholder="Name">
                        <input name="email" id="email" type="text" placeholder="Email">

                        <input class="submit" type="submit" value="SUBMIT">
                    </form>
                    <p class="form-messege"></p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<div id="about-area" class="all-about gray-bg">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="home-slider2 clearfix">
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-lg-7 col-md-6">
                    <div class="about-bottom-left clearfix">
                        <h1>about <span>Helpy</span></h1>
                        <h3>Helpy is more than just a dating app, it’s a platform dedicated to helping you become an intentional dater. </h3>
                        <p class="about-pb">Dating in today's digital age offers unparalleled opportunities to meet new people, but it also presents unique challenges. With countless profiles and endless swipes, it’s easy to feel like you’re caught in a cycle of surface-level connections. Intentional dating, however, provides a way to cut through the noise. By approaching dating with clarity and purpose, you can find a match who aligns with your values, goals, and specific needs. </p>
                        <p>One unique aspect of intentional dating is the ability to express and address financial intentions in a relationship. For some, this might mean helping a partner with their tuition, college fees, loans, groceries or other bills while for others, it may involve seeking a partner who can offer that kind of support. By openly and respectfully addressing these needs, intentional daters can build aligned connections. Let’s explore how intentional dating can guide both men and women in articulating and fulfilling these goals.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="col-lg-5 col-md-6">
                    <div class="about-bottom-img">
                        <img src="assets/img/feature1.jpg" alt="">
